## MEASUREMENT & METRICS EVERY TRADER SHOULD TRACK

### PERFORMANCE METRICS
| Metric | Formula | Target | Interpretation |
|--------|---------|--------|-----------------|
| Win Rate | Winners / Total Trades | 40-55% | Higher doesn't mean profitable |
| Profit Factor | Gross Profit / Gross Loss | >1.5 | Ensures profit after losses |
| Average Win/Loss Ratio | Avg Win $ / Avg Loss $ | 1:2 | Reward vs Risk |
| Expectancy | (Win% × Avg Win) - (Loss% × Avg Loss) | Positive | Average profit per trade |
| Risk-Reward Ratio | Target Profit / Stop Loss | 2:1 minimum | Defines edge |
| Max Drawdown | Biggest peak-to-trough loss | <20% | Worst case scenario |
| Recovery Factor | Total Profit / Max Drawdown | >2.0 | Ability to recover from losses |
| Sharpe Ratio | Return / Volatility | >1.0 | Consistency of returns |

### PSYCHOLOGICAL METRICS (From Journal)
- Rule adherence %: Should be 95%+ (deviations = losses)
- Emotional trading instances: Ideally 0
- Revenge trades per month: Ideally 0
- Position sizing violations: Ideally 0
- Trend bias accuracy: Track if daily trend prediction right

